    <taskbody>
        <steps>
            <step>
                <cmd>Highlight the text that you would like to tag as a <cmdname>Place</cmdname>.
                    Click on the toolbar or right-click options (see image below).<image
                        placement="break"
                        href="http://beta.cwrc.ca/islandora/object/cwrc%3Ae28153a3-d5b1-42ca-ad06-889c98c8ba0d/datastream/OBJ/view"
                        id="image_arl_lzw_mp" align="center"/><image placement="break"
                        href="http://beta.cwrc.ca/islandora/object/cwrc%3A2f46a0b5-7be1-4c10-916b-cb0272de845b/datastream/OBJ/view"
                        id="image_ttr_llv_tp" align="center"/></cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>Try to find the place you are tagging in the CWRC or GeoNames entries.<image
                        placement="break"
                        href="http://beta.cwrc.ca/islandora/object/cwrc%3A32233e19-cb52-454d-bee2-38052c606b3f/datastream/OBJ/view"
                        id="image_rjd_vws_pr" align="center"/></cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>If your entry is not in the CWRC entity lookup system you have the option to
                    create your own. To do this click on <cmdname>Create New Place</cmdname> button at the bottom of
                    that page.</cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>An "Add Place" pop-up appears, fill it out (see note) and click <cmdname>OK</cmdname>.</cmd>
                <info>The only mandatory field is the place name, though there are many other areas
                    that you can fill out.<image placement="break"
                        href="http://beta.cwrc.ca/islandora/object/cwrc%3A88f0c37f-613a-43d6-b04a-10ad51738a76/datastream/OBJ/view"
                        id="image_frn_2m2_lp" align="center" height="6in" width="4in"/></info>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>Once you have created a place entry in the CWRC entity repository, you can now
                    add more information about the tag (precision, person type, etc.). Click on
                        <cmdname>Save</cmdname>.<image placement="break"
                        href="http://beta.cwrc.ca/islandora/object/cwrc%3A38d90e91-61d7-4e36-8f89-201db1c3a814/datastream/OBJ/view"
                        id="image_qh3_4lv_tp" align="center"/></cmd>
            </step>
        </steps>
        <result>You have now created a new CWRC entity entry, you can use this creation the next
            time that you go to tag this person.<image placement="break"
                href="http://beta.cwrc.ca/islandora/object/cwrc%3Ae0d8baa3-cdff-4ed0-9cec-2e9294e38789/datastream/OBJ/view"
